#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:192
msgid "Managing purchase suggestions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:194
msgid "Purchase suggestions can be generated in one of two ways. You can create suggestions via the staff client either for the library or :ref:`on the patron's behalf <purchase-suggestions-label>` from their record. Depending on your settings in the :ref:`suggestion` system preference, patrons may also be able to make purchase suggestions via the OPAC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:203
msgid "You need to be logged in as a staff member with the suggestions_manage :ref:`acquisitions permission <patron-permissions-label>` in order to view and work with purchase suggestions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:207
msgid "If you have the suggestions_manage permission but not Acquisitions permissions you can access the suggestion management tool from Suggestions under the More menu in the header bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:210
msgid "When a suggestion is waiting for library review, it will appear on the Acquisitions home page next to the vendor search.  Clicking 'Manage suggestions' will take you to the suggestion management tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:214
msgid "|image794|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:216
msgid "It will also appear on the main staff dashboard under the module labels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:218
msgid "|image795|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:220
msgid "If there are no pending suggestions you can access the suggestion management tool by clicking the 'Manage suggestions' link on the menu on the left of the Acquisitions page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:224
msgid "|image796|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:228
msgid "You can customize the columns of this table in the :ref:`'Table settings'<column-settings-label>` section of the Administration module (table id: suggestions)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:232
msgid "Your suggestions will be sorted into several tabs: Accepted, Pending, Checked, Ordered and/or Rejected. Each accepted or rejected suggestion will show the name of the librarian who managed the suggestion and the reason they gave for accepting or rejecting it (found under 'Status')."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:237
msgid "An 'Accepted' suggestion is one that you have marked as 'Accepted' using the form below the suggestions. A 'Pending' suggestion is one that is awaiting action from the library. A 'Checked' suggestion is one that has been marked as 'Checked' using the form before the suggestions. An 'Ordered' suggestion is on that has been ordered using the '`From a purchase suggestion <#orderfromsuggestion>`__' link in your basket. A 'Rejected' suggestion is one that you have marked at 'Rejected' using the form below the list of suggestions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:246
msgid "For libraries with lots of suggestions, there are filters on the left hand side of the Manage Suggestions page to assist in limiting the number of titles displayed on the screen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:250
msgid "|image797|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:252
msgid "Clicking on the blue headings will expand the filtering options and clicking '[clear]' will clear all filters and show all suggestions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:257
msgid "The suggestions page will automatically be limited to suggestions for your library. To see information for all (or any other) libraries click on the 'Acquisition information' filter and change the library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:262
msgid "|image798|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:264
msgid "When reviewing 'Pending' suggestions you can choose to check the box next to the item(s) you want to approve/reject and then choose the status and reason for your selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:268
msgid "|image799|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:270
msgid "Reasons for accepting and rejecting suggestions are defined by the `SUGGEST <#suggestauthorized>`__ authorized value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:273
msgid "|image802|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:275
msgid "If you choose 'Others...' as your reason you will be prompted to enter your reason in a text box. Clicking 'Cancel' to the right of the box will bring back the pull down menu with authorized reasons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:279
msgid "|image803|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:281
msgid "You can also change the item type of the suggestions by selecting them and choosing the new item type in the 'Update item types with' drop down menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:284
msgid "|image1473|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:286
msgid "You can also change the manager of the selected suggestions by clicking the 'Select manager' link and searching your user database. Note that only users who have the 'superlibrarian' or the 'suggestions\\_manage' permission will show in the results. The new manager will receive the :ref:`NOTIFY\\_MANAGER notice<existing-notices-and-slips-label>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:291
msgid "You can also choose to completely delete the selected suggestions by clicking the 'Delete' button in the the 'Delete selected' box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:294
msgid "Another option for libraries with long lists of suggestions is to approve or reject suggestions one by one by clicking on the title of the suggestion to open a summary of the suggestion, including information if the item was purchased."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:299
msgid "|image800|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:301
msgid "Clicking 'edit' to the right of the suggested title or at the top of the suggestion detail page will open a suggestion editing page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:304
msgid "|image801|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:306
msgid "From this form you can make edits to the suggestion (adding more details or updating incorrect information provided by the patron). You can also choose to accept or reject the suggestion on an individual basis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:310
msgid "Choosing to mark a request as 'Pending' will move the request back to the 'Pending' tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:313
msgid "You can also assign this suggestion to a fund."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:315
msgid "|image1280|"
msgstr ""

