#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1487
msgid "EDI setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1489
msgid "Before you begin ordering using EDI you will want to take the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1492
msgid "Ask your vendor/bookseller/jobber for :ref:`connection information <edi-questions-for-vendors-label>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1495
msgid "It might also be beneficial to ask for a few sample EDIFACT files from the vendor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1498
msgid "Share with your vendor/bookseller/jobber your :ref:`library codes <libraries-label>`, :ref:`item type codes <item-types-label>`, :ref:`fund codes <funds-label>`, and any other codes or :ref:`authorized values <authorized-values-label>` they might need for creating your MARC order records"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1504
msgid "Communicate with your support provider or the community about whether you will need a plugin based on your vendor's answers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1507
msgid "For example ByWater Solutions has published plugins for specific vendors here: https://github.com/bywatersolutions/koha-plugin-edifact-enhanced"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1511
msgid ":ref:`Enter the vendor/bookseller/jobber <add-a-vendor-label>` in Acquisitions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1514
msgid "Review your :ref:`Acquisitions system preferences <acquisitions-system-preferences-label>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1516
msgid "Be sure to fill in the :ref:`MarcFieldsToOrder` preference with values for order files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1519
msgid "Enter your :ref:`EDI Accounts`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1521
msgid "Enter your :ref:`Library EANs`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1523
msgid "Turn on the :ref:`EDI Cron <cron-edi-message-processing-label>` so that it can process files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1528
msgid "EDI ordering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1530
msgid "The first step in ordering using EDI happens on the book vendor's website. Each seller will use different language, but you will need to place your order on their site and then download the MARC order file. Some language that you might see included \"basket\", \"order\", \"cart\", and/or \"MARC order.\" Once you have this MARC file downloaded to your computer you will want to log in to Koha and continue the process there."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1537
msgid "Visit the :ref:`Stage MARC records for import` tool and upload your file. Once presented with the confirmation screen proceed to Acquisitions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1541
msgid "In Acquisitions :ref:`create a basket <create-a-basket-label>` for the vendor you ordered from. From the basket, choose to `order from a staged file <#orderfromstagedfile>`__ and click 'Order' next to the file you downloaded from your vendor and staged in Koha."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1546
msgid "From the confirmation screen you will see all of the data in the MARC file related to your order. If you are not seeing fields such as fund and quantity filled in then be sure to confirm that your :ref:`MarcFieldsToOrder` preference is set right."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1551
msgid "Once you have added all of the items to the basket you can click the 'Create EDIFACT order' button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1557
msgid "Sending the EDIFACT order"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1559
msgid "This will generate a pending file in the :ref:`EDIFACT messages <edifact-messages-label>` in Koha. The pending files will be processed by the :ref:`EDI cron job <cron-edi-message-processing-label>` and sent to your vendor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1566
msgid "EDI ordering with Quote files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1568
msgid "If you have Quote files enabled you can place the order on the bookseller's website and a Quote file will be automatically generated and made available to be collected and loaded to Koha.  You will see the file listed in the :ref:`EDIFACT messages <edifact-messages-label>` in Koha with a status of 'Received'.  The basket will have been created and records and items added to the basket.  Once you have checked that the basket is correct you can click the 'Create EDIFACT order' button.  The process then completes as for :ref:`Sending the EDIFACT order <sending-the_edifact-order-label>` above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1579
msgid "EDI invoicing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1581
msgid "When the book vendor is done processing your files they will send an invoice via EDI as well. The :ref:`EDI cron job <cron-edi-message-processing-label>` will grab invoices and mark items found in the invoice as received and update your funds without any need for manual intervention."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1586
msgid "If you set the :ref:`EdifactInvoiceImport` preference to 'Don't' you can load invoice files manually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1591
msgid "EDIFACT messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/acquisitions.rst:1593
msgid "A log of all messages sent and received via EDIFACT can be found under EDIFACT messages."
msgstr ""

